**Hog--Island**.description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hog Island&lt;/strong&gt; Q986-533          Sheet 63 Little neighbour of Scattery Island and less interesting. A drumlinesque few acres, there are horses, Shelduck and goats. The island is privately owned and camping is not permitted. Rumours of a wind farm in January 2012 lack planning permission for corroboration.  All bushes and gorse on the island have been removed and a small breakwater wall is now located on the N side at the entrance to a salt marsh and lagoon that is navigable to kayaks at HW. Wildlife was good at the lagoon with 250+ Teal, 100 Widgeon, Snipe 30 and good numbers of Oystercatcher, Curlew, and Redshank roosting there at high water. Common Seals seen (4). Local HW is generally:&lt;/p&gt;
