&lt;p&gt;The fastest flow is at Darby’s Point, just inside the entrance. On the flood, a major eddy circulates just inside the Point at F723-935 on the Achill Island side, reaching as far as &lt;em&gt;Gránúaile&lt;/em&gt;’s castle at F721-941. The tide floods south through the northern entrance called Bull’s Mouth F737-068 at up to 5kn.&lt;/p&gt;
